'''Tarik Muharemović''' ({{IPA|bs|tâːrik muxâːremoʋitɕ|pron}}; born 28 February 2003) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for [[Serie A]] club [[US Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]]. Born in Slovenia, he plays for the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

Muharemović started his professional career at [[Wolfsberger AC]], playing mainly in its reserve team, before joining [[Juventus Next Gen]] in 2021, who loaned him to Sassuolo in 2024, with whom he signed permanently the following year.

A former youth international for Bosnia and Herzegovina, Muharemović made his senior international debut in 2024, earning 14 [[Cap (sport)|caps]] since.

==Club career==

===Early career===
Muharemović started playing football at local clubs, before joining [[Wolfsberger AC|Wolfsberger AC's youth setup]] in 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/330415-talijani-prenose-da-je-tarik-muharemovic-novi-igrac-juventusa|title=Talijani prenose da je Tarik Muharemović novi igrač Juventusa|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=12 July 2021|accessdate=15 July 2021|language=Bosnian}}</ref> He made his professional debut against [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]] on 25 April 2021 at the age of 18.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/roden-u-ljubljani-zeljela-ga-i-austrija-slovenci-pisu-da-ce-mladi-fudbaler-igrati-za-bih/91086|title=Rođen u Ljubljani, željela ga i Austrija: Slovenci pišu da će mladi fudbaler igrati za BiH|website=faktor.ba|date=29 May 2021|access-date=1 June 2021|language=bs}}</ref>

===Juventus===
In August 2021, Muharemović moved to Italian side [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] on a four-year deal.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/tarik-muharemovic-potpisao-za-juventus-na-cetiri-godine/210810161|title=Tarik Muharemović potpisao za Juventus na četiri godine|website=klix.ba|date=11 August 2021|access-date=12 August 2021|language=bs}}</ref> On 11 December 2022, he scored his first professional goal playing for [[Juventus Next Gen|Juventus' reserve squad]] against [[FC Arzignano Valchiampo|Arzignano]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/377403-tarik-muharemovic-postigao-prvi-gol-u-dresu-juventusa|title=Tarik Muharemović postigao prvi gol u dresu Juventusa|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=11 December 2022|access-date=12 December 2022|language=bs}}</ref>

In September 2023, he signed a new three-year contract with the team.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/857526/talentovani-tarik-muharemovic-potpisao-novi-ugovor-s-juventusom|title=Talentovani Tarik Muharemović potpisao novi ugovor s Juventusom|website=avaz.ba|date=26 September 2023|access-date=28 September 2023|language=bs}}</ref>

===Sassuolo===
In August 2024, Muharemović was sent on a season-long loan to [[US Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/tarik-muharemovic-presao-iz-juventusa-u-sassuolo/196458|title=Tarik Muharemović prešao iz Juventusa u Sassuolo|website=faktor.ba|date=28 August 2024|access-date=30 August 2024|language=bs}}</ref> He made his official debut for the squad on 21 September against [[Cosenza Calcio|Cosenza]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/440412-tarik-muharemovic-debitovao-za-novi-tim-u-italiji|title=Tarik Muharemović debitovao za novi tim u Italiji|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=21 September 2024|access-date=24 September 2024|language=bs}}</ref> On 24 September, he scored his first goal for the outfit in a [[2024–25 Coppa Italia#Second round|Coppa Italia]] game against [[US Lecce|Lecce]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/tarik-muharemovic-postigao-prvijenac-za-sassuolo-video|title=Tarik Muharemović postigao prvijenac za Sassuolo|website=n1info.ba|date=24 September 2024|access-date=25 September 2024|language=bs}}</ref> Three months later, he scored his first league goal in a triumph over [[US Salernitana 1919|Salernitana]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/950322/muharemovic-postigao-gol-nakon-sjajne-akcije-sassuolo-grabi-ka-serie-a|title=Muharemović postigao gol nakon sjajne akcije, Sassuolo grabi ka Serie A|website=avaz.ba|date=12 January 2025|access-date=15 January 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

In April 2025, Sassuolo signed him on a multi-year deal.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/sassuolo-za-pet-miliona-eura-od-juventusa-otkupio-tarika-muharemovica/496372|title=Sassuolo za pet miliona eura od Juventusa otkupio Tarika Muharemovića|website=sportsport.ba|date=14 April 2025|access-date=15 April 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

Muharemović was an important piece in Sassuolo's conquest of the [[2024–25 Serie B|Serie B]] title, his first trophy with the club, which was secured on 4 May and earned them promotion to the [[2025–26 Serie A|Serie A]] just one season after being relegated.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/465787-muharemovic-i-zvanicno-sa-sassuolom-osvojio-serie-b|title=Muharemović i zvanično sa Sassuolom osvojio Serie B|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=4 May 2025|access-date=4 May 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

In October, he extended his contract with the side until June 2031.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/nagradjen-za-odlicne-igre-u-serie-a-muharemovic-produzio-ugovor-sa-sassuolom/251031140|title=Nagrađen za odlične igre u Serie A: Muharemović produžio ugovor sa Sassuolom|website=klix.ba|date=31 October 2025|access-date=1 November 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

==International career==
Muharemović represented [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] at various youth levels. He also served as a [[Captain (association football)|captain]] of the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national under-21 football team|under-21 team]] under coach [[Vinko Marinović]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oslobodjenje.ba/sport/fudbal/reprezentacija/tarik-muharemovic-uzori-su-mi-emir-spahic-i-edin-dzeko-990351|title=Tarik Muharemović: Uzori su mi Emir Spahić i Edin Džeko|website=oslobodjenje.ba|date=13 October 2024|access-date=15 October 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

In May 2024, he received his first senior call up, for [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] games against [[England national football team|England]] and [[Italy national football team|Italy]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/ovo-je-barbarezov-spisak-za-englesku-i-italiju-pozvano-sedam-novih-zmajeva/545686|title=Ovo je Barbarezov spisak za Englesku i Italiju: Pozvano sedam novih Zmajeva|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=16 May 2024|access-date=18 May 2024|language=bs}}</ref> He debuted against the former on 3 June.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/engleska-slavila-protiv-bih-zmajevi-u-barbarezovom-debiju-za-pola-sata-potopljeni-u-newcastleu/189628|title=Engleska slavila protiv BiH: Zmajevi u Barbarezovom debiju za pola sata potopljeni u Newcastleu|website=faktor.ba|date=3 June 2024|access-date=4 June 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

On 10 June 2025, in a friendly match against [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]], he scored his first senior international goal.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/979189/slovenija-u-prijateljskoj-utakmici-savladala-bosnu-i-hercegovinu|title=Slovenija u prijateljskoj utakmici savladala Bosnu i Hercegovinu|website=avaz.ba|date=10 June 2025|access-date=10 June 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

In June 2026, Muharemović was named in Bosnia and Herzegovina's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/barbarez-poslao-konacan-spisak-fifa-i-jedno-ime-otputovalo-u-ameriku-ali-nije-na-listi|title=Barbarez poslao konačan spisak FIFA-i: Jedno ime otputovalo u Ameriku, ali nije na listi|website=sportske.ba|date=3 June 2026|access-date=3 June 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Muharemović's mother is originally from [[Sanski Most]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=Sanski Most ponosan na Tarika Muharemovića |url=https://inmedia.ba/sanski-most-ponosan-na-tarika-muharemovica/ |access-date=2026-06-06 |language=bs-BA}}</ref> and his father is from [[Zavidovići]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Zdici.info {{!}} Tarik Muharemović, porijeklom iz Zavidovića, potpisao za Juventus |url=https://zdici.info/tarik-muharemovic-porijeklom-iz-zavidovica-potpisao-za-juventus |access-date=2026-06-06 |website=zdici.info |language=en}}</ref> His younger brother Kenan is also a professional footballer.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/brat-bh-reprezentativca-potpisao-za-rapid-iz-beca/191709|title=Brat bh. reprezentativca potpisao za Rapid iz Beča|website=faktor.ba|date=29 June 2024|access-date=1 July 2024|language=bs}}</ref> 

He is a practising [[Islam|Muslim]]; together with international teammates [[Amar Dedić]], [[Ermedin Demirović]] and [[Dženis Burnić]] he visited a [[mosque]] in [[Sarajevo]] during the national team's concentration.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/zmajevi-snimljeni-na-dzumi-dedic-demirovic-muharemovic-i-burnic-bili-u-dzamiji-u-sarajevu/639157|title=Zmajevi snimljeni na džumi: Dedić, Demirović, Muharemović i Burnić bili u džamiji u Sarajevu|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=29 May 2026|access-date=1 June 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

